# Firebase Admin SDK (Firestore) credentials.
#
# On Vercel (recommended): paste the ENTIRE service-account JSON as the value
# of the FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT env var (set it in Vercel -> Settings ->
# Environment Variables). Do NOT paste each field separately.
#
# For local dev: copy this file to .env.local and fill in either of the two
# modes below.

# Mode 1 (recommended for Vercel): entire service account as a single string.
# In Vercel, store the service-account JSON content as the value of this
# env var (Vercel supports multi-line env vars; the JSON may be one line or
# many). Get this JSON from:
#   Firebase console -> Project settings -> Service accounts tab
#   -> "Generate new private key" -> download -> copy the file contents here.
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT=

# Mode 2 (alternative): GCP standard — path to a service account JSON file
# on disk. Useful for local dev when you don't want to inline the JSON.
# GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS=/path/to/serviceAccountKey.json
